PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F436A1770303096
OL,3,CTeachers on strike over 'abusive pupil
OL,4,Cbehaviour threatening safety' of staff
OL,6,F"In order to avoid further action,
OL,7,Fmanagement need to start to take
OL,8,Fseriously their duty of care to their
OL,9,Fstaff and to put in place a pupil
OL,10,Fbehaviour management system which
OL,11,Feffectively tackles any form of abuse
OL,12,Fand upholds the right of teachers to
OL,13,Fbe able to get on with their job in
OL,14,Fsafety."
OL,16,FWendy Exton, NASUWT National Executive
OL,17,FMember for Gloucestershire, added:
OL,18,F"Staff want to teach and give their
OL,19,Fbest to their students, but the
OL,20,Fcontinual disruption is preventing
OL,21,Fthem from doing so.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@HO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
